host_about:
Greetings from the Veeve team!


Veeve manage the largest collection of homes to rent for short stays in London since 2011, launching in Paris in 2017. Our rental homes are predominantly privately-owned, lived-in homes in vibrant neighbourhoods. Thanks to our fully managed service, when you stay in a Veeve property you can benefit from the spaciousness, personal style and relaxed feel of a home – but with all the amenities of a hotel.


Once a booking is confirmed our Customer Service team will become your main point of contact and get in touch with you to organise your arrival at the property (including airport transfers, upon request); after which our on-the-ground management team will look after all aspects of your stay, with in-stay support available to help with any queries.


We have strict cleanliness guidelines for our cleaners and all staff who enter our properties and have reinforced existing cleaning procedures in line with official WHO, British and French government guidance.


As always, our team ensure that all properties are cleaned to a professional standard before and after each stay, with increased focus on touch-point cleaning (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.).

 All staff who enter properties will follow the below procedures:
 

- Carry and regularly use alcohol-based hand rub
- Sanitise their mobile phones 
- Focus extra attention when cleaning key touch-point areas (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.)
- Wear protective gear where appropriate
- Wash and disinfect work shoes


We might be able to arrange for property viewings, upon request, for stays of over 28 nights. 

Please be aware once a booking is confirmed you will be required to complete a Rental Agreement and also  ID verification via our partners Superhog. This is mandatory for all our stays and in accordance to short lets requirements with Veeve.

If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us and we will be sure to answer you promptly.

name: charmant appart 5 min de Notre Dame
description:
Charmant 3 pièces de 57m², 3ème étage sans ascenseur à 5 min à pied de notre dame, au cœur du quartier latin. Point de départ idéal pour visiter Paris.

The space
Appartement au 3ème étage sans ascenseur typiquement parisien avec du parquet, où il fait bon se reposer. Son emplacement est agréable dans ce quartier animé!

Il se compose d'une entrée donnant sur un salon/salle à manger. Vous y aurez accès à:
- écran plat avec plus de 100 chaînes câblées ( Langue anglaise possible)
- 1 canapé convertible très confortable 160/200cm
- 1 table à manger 4/6 personnes
- 2 chaises hautes pour enfants
Ce salon donne ensuite accès à la chambre à coucher:
- Avec un vrai lit 160/200cm
- Une armoire où mettre vos habits
- Une salle de bain en carrelage blanc avec 1 fenêtre, une baignoire, sèche- cheveux et sèche serviette.
- table à langer
Linge, serviettes, gants de toilettes et savon sont inclus dans la location.
neighborhood_overview:
Cet appartement est situé à 5 min de Notre Dame , au cœur du quartier latin dans le centre de Paris. Vous aurez donc à votre disposition toutes les commodités dans la même rue: boulangerie, boucherie, poissonnerie, fromager, supermarchés... Ainsi que de multiples transports pour visiter le reste de la capitale (Stations Vélib', Métro, RER, Bus).
Le cadre de l'emplacement reste idéal pour découvrir la vie parisienne, avec ses nombreux restaurants et bars à proximité. Berceau culturel de la capitale, vous serez entourés entre autre des plus grandes écoles telles la Sorbonne ou encore Henri IV, mais aussi de grands espaces verts comme le Jardin du luxembourg et le jardin des plantes.

Bien évidemment, si vous avez des questions concernant votre confort pendant le séjour je reste à votre entière disposition en espérant vous souhaiter la bienvenue très bientôt !
host_about: Travaillant et vivant dans le quartier latin depuis plus de dix ans, je pourrais vous conseiller sur quelques bonnes adresses à coté de l’appartement!!!

Located in a homy and calm neighborhood in the 12th arrondissement, 2 min from the nearest metro station and 10 min from the famous Place de la Nation (public transport leading to everywhere in Paris), our flat is a calm and a full of light haven. It has a big luminous living room with a dining area and an open kitchen, a bedroom, a guest room/office with a sofa-bed for 2 people, bathroom and toilet.

The space
Our flat has been recently renovated to have a loft-like look with wide open space and combining the style of typical parisian (our building is from the 1900s, with original hard wood floors and fireplace) and scandinavian cozy interior design. It is on the 5th floor (no elevator, sorry but it is typical of old Paris building ;)) which provides the advantage of great light (East-West exposure) in the big living room. neighborhood_overview: The 12th arrondissement is located in the south-east of Paris and is well known for being a calm, family-friendly and mercantile area while being close to the vibrant Parisian life of the 11th (many of the best restaurants and bars in Paris being there) and very accessible to the animated center of the city. Our neighborhood is very typical of the 12th : friendly and calm, many convenience stores around (supermarkets, bakeries, markets, pharmacies etc) and a few gems in terms of restaurants and cafés.

neighborhood_overview:
The Marais district
The Marais district gets its name from its location: once a marshland (‘marais’), it has been inhabited ever since it was drained back in the 12th century. This historic area is now one of the most visited districts of the French capital, for its architectural heritage as well as its unique vibe. The district is shaped like a triangle, bordered respectively by Place de la Bastille, Place de la République and the Hôtel de Ville. It has a number of private mansions dating to the 17th and 18th centuries, some of which have been converted into internationally renowned museums such as the Musée Picasso, the Maison de Victor Hugo and the Musée Carnavalet. The beautiful and well-proportioned square known as Place des Vosges is a highlight of a stroll through the Marais. Rue des Rosiers, the Jewish quarter of Paris, is well worth exploring for its old-world atmosphere and its offbeat shops and restaurants. host_about:
L'établissement Le 123 Sébastopol - Astotel est situé dans le IIe arrondissement de Paris, à 150 mètres de la station de métro Réaumur-Sébastopol et 10 minutes à pied de la place de la République. Il possède une terrasse, une bagagerie et une réception ouverte 24h/24.

Affichant une décoration inspirée du cinéma, les chambres climatisées disposent d'une station d'accueil pour iPod, d'une télévision à écran plat et d'un minibar avec des boissons sans alcool gratuites. Leur salle de bains privative est pourvue d'un sèche-cheveux. Chaque étage rend hommage à un artiste de cinéma spécifique.

Un petit-déjeuner buffet est préparé chaque matin. Vous pourrez également le savourer dans le confort de votre chambre. Des restaurants sont accessibles en quelques minutes de marche. De l'après-midi jusque tard en soirée, vous aurez l'occasion de déguster gracieusement des boissons sans alcool et des collations dans le hall de l'hôtel. Ce service est aussi disponible dans tous les établissements Astotel de Paris.

Le 123 Sébastopol - Astotel propose un ascenseur, des quotidiens gratuits et une connexion Wi-Fi gratuite dans l'ensemble des locaux. Le centre commercial Les Halles est à 10 minutes à pied, tandis que le musée du Louvre se trouve à 1,5 km.

Ce quartier (2e arr.) est un choix idéal pour les voyageurs qui s'intéressent à ces thèmes : le shopping, l'art et l'architecture.

 (Website hidden by Airbnb) ****

Located in the 2nd district of Paris, just 150 m from Réamur-Sébastopol Metro Station, 123 Sébastopol offers a terrace, 24-hour reception and luggage storage. Place de la République is only a 10-minute walk away.

With a cinema-inspired décor, all rooms are air-conditioned and feature an iPod docking station, a flat-screen TV, and a minibar with free soft drinks. The en suite bathroom includes a hairdryer. Each floor pays tribute to a specific cinema artist and each room includes complimentary non-alcoholic beverages in the minibar.

A buffet breakfast is served each morning at 123 Sébastopol and it can also be enjoyed in the comfort of your own room. Restaurants can be found within walking distance. Starting in the afternoon until late in the evening, guests can also enjoy free non-alcoholic beverages and snacks in the hotel lobby. Guests can stop by any of Astotel's hotels in Paris to enjoy this service and have a drink or snack, free of charge.

neighborhood_overview: The Latin Quarter in the 5th arrondissement, on the Left Bank. The area’s many cafés and restaurants are laid-back and welcoming; they are filled with Parisians, students and tourists. There are several attractions to visit, among them the Pantheon, the Musée National du Moyen-Âge, the Luxembourg gardens and museum and the Arènes de Lutèce. As you stroll through the district you will also come across the Sorbonne, the best known university in Paris; the Collège de France, the Lycée Henri IV, the shopping streets Rue Mouffetard and Rue Monge and the charming Place de la Contrescarpe. The district also has popular show venues like the Paradis Latin, the Théâtre de l’Odéon and the Caveau de la Huchette.

neighborhood_overview:
🌳 🍁 Père Lachaise: With more than 70,000 graves spread over 44 hectares, Père Lachaise is the largest cemetery in Paris and the most visited in the world! In this unusual walk we propose you to discover the mythical characters that made its history and fame.
From the main entrance on Boulevard Ménilmontant to the Gambetta exit, we invite you to cross this gigantic open-air museum, stopping at the most emblematic burials. From the most romantic to the most mystical to the most photographed, or the most floral, the selected anecdotes will help you understand why these tombs have given rise to sometimes surprising traditions or true cults.

host_about: Hotel Marignan, in the Keniger family since 1955, has been a meeting place for international guests since its opening.   Because of the ideal location of the hotel near la Sorbonne in the historical center of Paris, many intellectuals, writers, artists, students and academics have stayed in the hotel. The famous American poet e. e Cummings, the French/Romanian philosopher, Emil Cioran, the painter, Mordecai Ardon, the writer and director Tadeusz Konwicki, the artist and theater director Tadeusz Kantor, the poet Avrom Sutzkever, Zorba the Greek author Nikos Kazantzakis and the anthropologist Jacques Ruffié have all stayed in our hotel over the years.

description:
This three-bedroom is unique. It is located in the medieval district of ‘Le Marais’ in a culturally rich area, with museums not very far away.

This 100m² wooden-floored apartment is set up to welcome up to 6 guests. It is very bright and is nicely decorated and furnished with quality pieces of furniture. It is on the 2nd floor (2 flights of stairs) of a stone building .

The space
On entering the apartment, one finds a room with a large windows that offers a desk and closets where coats can be hanged and luggage may be stored.
When entering in the living are which is a few steps further down, one is welcomed by a warm and large size living room. It offers 3 distinct areas, into the lounge area, the dining area and the open kitchen.

The living area offers a large comfortable sofa, an arm chair and a sitting chair, TV, warm lighting and a modern coffee table. It is adorned by a lovely fire place and a lovely abstract painting. It is a per
neighborhood_overview:
The location is incredible. One cannot dream of a better location with the choice of shops, restaurant and bars. Visit le “Marché des enfants rouges” a great place for shopping or go to shows à the “Carreau du temple” at 5 mn walk. More over many museums and historic places are nearby - Musée Beaubourg, Picasso, Place des Vosges, Ile Saint Louis, Notre Dame Cathedral.

You will find a mix of cultural attractions, hype bars and night life, fancy clothes stores and traditional architecture. The “Seine” is 3 mn walking distance. neighborhood_overview:
﻿The 7th arrondissement is located in the heart of the French capital, along the left bank. It is the most populated, the most expensive and with the fewest shops in Paris! This does not make it any less a Parisian nugget for offering a great, if not unmatched, quality of life. Located in the heart of the most beautiful monuments of the capital, at the foot of the Eiffel Tower, with its private mansions entrenched behind high walls, gardens and secret courtyards, the 7th arrondissement remains a paradise for those who believe in the adage "let's live happily, let's live hidden"! You can visit the Rodin and Orsay museums, the Eiffel Tower, the Alexandre 3 Bridge and the Grand Palais and the most beautiful avenue in the world: the Champs Elysées. Whether it is Champ de Mars, Breteuil, Invalides or Saint Thomas d'Aquin, it is good to live in this green, calm, spacious but nevertheless very lively and therefore popular area of Paris!

In this district, you will not miss anything
host_about:
Mon Petit Faré est un service de conciergerie spécialisé en location courte durée.

C’est l’histoire d’une rencontre de deux passionnés de tourisme et d’hôtellerie en plein milieu du Pacifique, plus précisément en Polynésie à Tahiti.

Le faré désignant la maison traditionnelle polynésienne, Mon Petit Faré se veut ainsi diffuseur de la gentillesse et de la convivialité polynésienne à travers son offre de conciergerie.

En 2021 Mon Petit Faré a été sélectionné en tant qu'expert de gestion locative par le programme Luckey by Airbnb, devenant ainsi partenaire local et proposant son catalogue de biens à des millions de voyageurs. 

Les équipes de Mon Petit Faré ont suivi une formation rigoureuse, afin que les voyageurs bénéficient d'un accueil de la plus haute qualité.

Axé sur l'expérience et les avis clients, nous mettons en valeur les appartements que nous gérons pour le compte de nos clients (propriétaires des biens que nous vous proposons sur Airbnb) pour vous faire passer des séjours incroyables à Paris !

Notre valeur ajoutée :	
- un service de taxi dédié aux guests pour leur accompagnement à chaque étape de leur séjour
- un guide d’accueil personnalisé de l’appartement montrant des recommandations uniques, des adresses inédites
- un guide touristique à votre disposition
- un service de bagagerie
- des attentions particulières pour tout type de séjour (ménage en cours de séjour, réservations de restaurants…)

Chez Mon Petit Faré, savoir recevoir et partager n’est pas seulement un travail mais un devoir et un plaisir quotidien.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Mon Petit Faré is a concierge service specialized in short term rentals.

It is the story of a meeting between two tourism and hotel enthusiasts in the middle of the Pacific, more precisely in Polynesia, Tahiti. 

The faré designating the traditional Polynesian house, Mon Petit Faré wants to spread the Polynesian kindness and conviviality through its concierge service.

In 2021 Mon Petit Faré was selected as a rental management expert by the Luckey by Airbnb program, becoming a local partner and offering its catalog of properties to millions of travelers. 

Mon Petit Faré's teams have undergone rigorous training to ensure that travelers receive the highest quality of welcome.

Focused on experience and customer reviews, we highlight the apartments we manage on behalf of our clients (owners of the properties we offer on Airbnb) to make sure you have an incredible stay in Paris!

Our added value

- a tourist guide at your disposal

At Mon Petit Faré, knowing how to receive and share is not only a job but a duty and a daily pleasure.

You enter the apartment into a foyer that gives you access to the all the rooms sep
neighborhood_overview:
THE LOCATION AND NEIGHBORHOOD
La Camille is just minutes away from the Place des Vosges, the Musée Carnavalet (recently reopened), Musée Picasso, Musée Victor Hugo, the Maison Européenne de la Photographie, galleries, restaurants and shops.
It’s an easy stroll to Notre Dame, the Museum of Jewish Art and History, Arts et Métiers, Ile St. Louis, Canal Saint Martin, the Centre Pompidou, and many more. The area is France’s largest historical district and home to a 700 year old Jewish quarter. The 17th century architecture is a magnificent backdrop to all that the neighborhood has to offer.

The Cité de la Mode et du Design is a group of cultural programs. We find there the Galliera museum outside the walls, workshops, the Wanderlust as well as snacking spaces and a roof top quite pleasant the beautiful days.

neighborhood_overview:
Mon logement est proche de la Rue Montorgueil (rue piétonne qui est le cœur commerçant du quartier, et certains magasins font partie des plus vieux de Paris. Au n°38 de la rue par exemple se trouve « l’escargot Montorgueil », cuisine favorite au 20ème siècle de Guitry, Proust, Dali… et dont le plafond que vous pouvez voir à l’entrée est la peinture qui ornait la salle à manger de Sarah Bernhardt !), Le Barav
Construite en 1686, la place des Victoires est peut-être la plus connu des 5 places Royales de Paris, la plus imposante et la plus majestueuse que ses illustres soeurs la Place Vendôme ou la Place de la Concorde.
Vous y découvrirez de superbes bâtiments typiques de l’architecture du 17e siècle (appelée style Louis XIV) ainsi qu’une conception circulaire générale qui fut une véritable innovation architecturale à l’époque de sa construction.

La rue Saint-Denis est l’une des plus anciennes rues de la ville : son axe est tracé dès le Ier siècle par les Romaines. Il s’agit de la voie triomphale des entrées royales dans la capitale. Ancien au lieu de la prostitution parisienne, le quartier est en pleine évolution avec l’ouverture de nouveaux bars et restaurants de qualité.
Le passage Sainte-Foy existe dès le Moyen-Age. Il prend son nom actuel en 1873. Au début du XXe siècle, le passage accueille des commerces d’alimentation, puis des ateliers de confection (en cours de disparition). Le passage est actuellement en rénovation afin de retrouver sa superbe.
Le 2ème arrondissement de Paris est un historiquement l’un des centres financiers d’Europe, abritant l’ancien Palais de la Bourse, aujourd’hui appelé Palais Brogniart.
Le 2ème accueille également la célèbre rue Saint-Anne, connue des parisiens comme étant le repaire de restaurants et magasins japonais.

description:
Show up and start living from day one in Paris with this exquisite one-bedroom Blueground apartment. You’ll love coming home to this thoughtfully furnished, beautifully designed, and fully-equipped Sentier - Montorgueil home. (#PAR3)

The space
As with any Blueground apartment, you’ll find a thoughtfully designed space complete with beautiful furniture and a fully-equipped kitchen in this one-bedroom property. And, thanks to our superior quality mattresses, luxury linens, and towels, you can relax knowing you’ll always feel comfortably at home. When you’re ready for some fun, you can take in the Paris vibes or bring the entertainment to you with the premium wireless speaker or smart TV. This apartment also offers in-apartment laundry.

Please check the house rules as fees may apply for the building amenities.
neighborhood_overview: A symbol of the Sentier-Montorgueil area of the 1st and 2nd arrondissements, Rue Montorgeuil is a foodie’s mecca. A top-rate greengrocer, butcher, baker and the Pâtisserie Stohrer (the city’s oldest) are all at your doorstep. This pedestrianized block buzzes by night and on the weekends thanks to its bistro patios, restaurants and cafés of quintessentially Parisian and hipster traditions. Leisure aside, this furnished apartment is well placed to a number of Rue du Sentier startups and the offices of AFP. Metro lines 3 and 4 pass through Sentier-Montorgueil with quick connections to the RER network via Châtelet-Les Halles.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

Staying in the 9th arrondissement, you will be in the heart of one of the capital's liveliest neighborhoods. Numerous designer boutiques, restaurants, bars, cafés, entertainment... are all within walking distance. You can also walk to the Moulin Rouge, the Montorgueil district, Montmartre or even Notre-Dame. You will only need to take the metro to discover the historic centre of Paris, the Père-Lachaise cemetery, the Place de la Bastille, but also the Champs-Elysées, the Eiffel Tower and all the great monuments that make Paris the most beautiful city in the world.

neighborhood_overview: à quelques pas de la butte Montmartre et du quartier branché de la rue Lepic, des Abesses, le quartier est cependant préservé de l'agitation (on y entend le chant du merle tous les matins), et se consacre aux commerces alimentaires de qualité, à de petites boutiques et de nombreux restaurants conviviaux. Au détour d'une rue en revenant d'acheter une baguette, vous serez surpris par une perspective plongeante ou un escalier caché qui accède à un coin secret de Montmartre. L'un des plus charmants cinémas de Paris est trois rues, et la place de Clichy, de l'autre côté d'un pont métallique célèbre propose brasserie et multiplexe. On aura enjambé le cimetière de Montmartre, où l'on peut voir les tombes de Berlioz, Fred Chichin, Dalida, Degas, Dumas, Feydeau, France Gall et Michel Berger, les frères Goncourt, Sacha Guitry, Jeanne Moreau, Offenbach, Picabia, des bourreaux de Paris, Stendhal, François Truffaut ou encre Emile Zola...
host_about: Quinquagénaire parisien,  amoureux fidèle de Paris, mais voyageant beaucoup dans le monde entier, pour mon travail ou pour mes loisirs.  Je suis arrivé récemment dans ce joli studio que j'amėnage afin d'avoir de beaux volumes,  des couleurs délicates, de la lumière et un  quartier commerçant et vivant mais tranquille, à  deux pas des Abesses trėpidantes...

name: Space, confort, sun, calm ! and so Parisian …
description:
Proud to offer our visitors from all over the world to share our parisian way of life ! (and love it !)
Experience an authentic parisien area nearby river Seine and Eiffel Tower amongst many famous places. Enjoy a quiet and sunny home, overlooking all south of Paris and free parking. Only few minutes away from excellent food shops, nice cafés & restaurants rue de Lourmel, gorgeous open air market twice a week and luxurious Beaugrenelle Mall for great shopping, snacks and movies.

The space
Charming, cool, quiet and sunny flat, near the river, renovated in 2000 and 2014, with two nice double bedrooms, two bathrooms, a fully equipped kitchen and a great living and dining room with balcony and a wide view towards south of Paris.
We have a private parking lot for one car (only available on request) and access to a bicycle safe storage room in the building.

Guest access
A few minutes away from subway, bus, train and cabs stations, al
neighborhood_overview:
Cool and authentic area nearby the Seine river, with excellent food and wine shops, an open air market twice a week. The ultimate parisian shopping center is 5 minutes walk, with great shops, cafés and restaurants, and a new multiplex cinema. And a lot to see a part the Eiffel Tower and some of the main museums and touristic places.
Champs de Mars park is nearby with space and beautiful trees and old buildings around. Jogging or walking is also recommended on the riverside walk. And boatcruises to other areas of Paris start from the Quai de Grenelle.
host_about:
bonjour,

J'aime beaucoup faire le marché et la cuisine et François est un amateur de vins.  Nos intérêts sont plutôt culturels et vous trouverez toutes sortes de livres et de disques dans notre maison quand vous aurez un moment de repos.

name: Boutique family luxury in the heart of Montmartre
description:
This is a new and beautifully renovated, spacious 3 or 4 bedroomed family apartment with a luxurious boutique feel. It's situated on the middle of la rue des Abbesses. This is the most central and one of the most beautiful and vibrant streets in the heart of Montmartre, bubbling with cafes, restaurants, market-food and shops.

The space
This is a very spacious, 124m family home that's been recently renovated by a French photographer and his English wife with beautiful details and a real attention to detail. With windows everywhere it's very light and airy. There is one comfortable double bedroom for parents with queenside bed, 2 kids rooms with single beds. It comfortably accommodates 4 adults and two kids. The kids rooms are at the end of a corridor (filled with books and toys) so kids get their own space (and you get yours!). There is also a double sofa-bed in the spare room/office and there are two extra single kids' single mattresses for bigger families. There
neighborhood_overview: The apartment is right on the middle of rue des abbesses- one of the most beautiful, lively and artsy roads right in the heart of Montmartre. You will find many cafes and restaurants, food-stalls, cinemas and there is always something going on in this vibrant neighborhood! You are of course within 5-10 minutes walk of all the Montmartre tourist attractions- from le sacré cœur to Van Gogh and Picasso's dwellings, to le moulin rouge and all the exotic and erotic culture that Pigalle has to offer. You are within 5 minutes of 3 metro lines so getting around Paris is very easy. In fact you can walk to many of the central paris attractions in less than an hour. Brilliantly vibrant, and steeped in history and culture, Montmartre is simply one of the best neighborhoods in Paris to stay in.

host_about:
* MERCI de m'envoyer un message avant de réaliser votre réservation et je m'engage à vous répondre rapidement.
# Originaire de l'Ouest de la France sur la côte Atlantique (Vendée), voilà près de 15 ans que je vis sur Paris. Habitant au coeur de la Capitale, je suis sûr que comme moi, vous apprécierez vous y ballader, tant de nombreux lieux sont accessibles à pied. Ainsi, j'aime à rejoindre les quais de Seine en redescendant la rue Oberkampf, puis traversant le Marais, avant de voir enfin le haut des clochers de Notre Dame, derrière l'Hôtel de Ville. Tout comme j'apprécie également passer du temps dans mon Quartier ; considéré par certains comme un lieu "bobo", il est également celui des parisiens qui, sortant du bureau, se donnent rendez-vous dans les nombreux bars et restaurants. Bref, Nous aurons peut-être l'occasion de nous rencontrer et moi le plaisir de vous accueillir, pour que vous découvriez de vous même mon lieu de vie. A bientôt. FRED
° compte twiter @FBO75 : pour me suivre et découvrir Paris en images.

*******************************************************************************************
* PLEASE, leave me a message before sending your booking and I promise you a quick reply.
# Native from Western France, from the Atlantic coast (Vendée), I've been living in Paris for almost 15 years now. I really appreciate the place I am living in as, being in the center of the French capital city, I have access to many of its beauties, which are within walking distance from my flat ; I am sure you will enjoy it too! I particularly love going down the OBERKAMPF street, then through the Marais district, to reach the Seine and catching glimpse of the Notre Dame towers behind the City Hall. But I also appreciate spending time in my neighbourhood ; considered by some as a "BoBo" place, it is above all one of the Parisians who wish to meet for a drink after work. In short, I hope we'll have the opportunity to meet so that you discover by yourselves my living place. See you soon. FRED
° follow me on twiter and discover Paris in pictures everyday : @FBO75

neighborhood_overview:
In a few months, the Oberkampf district has become very "trendy", overcrowded at weekends and strong by its diversity, its warm atmosphere and its low prices. As in fifteen local bars, there are free shows and concerts every night.
Ménilmontant, Parmentier, discover the Oberkampf district in Paris, tourist, festive and night owl district close to the very busy rue Jean-Pierre Timbaud and Belleville. The popular menilmuch has become a playground for young people and those who like to have fun, Paris by night.
Between 5 and 15 min. by metro you can find: The Saint Germain des Près neighborhood, the Opéra Garnier, the Galeries Lafayette, the Place Vendôme, the Place de la Concorde, the Champs-Elysées, Montmartre, the Eiffel Tower, etc.
Between 5 and 30 minutes on foot you will find: The Les Halles, the Louvre, the Palais Royal, the Pont Neuf, the Seine, the Marais, the Notre-Dame Cathedral, the Musée Beaubourg/Centre Pompidou, the Pont des Arts, the Place des Victoires, etc
